SNoW - Sparse Network of Winnows
Version 3.1.4
For questions or bug reports about the SNoW software, contact Nick Rizzolo
(rizzolo@cs.uiuc.edu)

University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign
Department of Computer Science
Dr. Dan Roth - Cognitive Computation Group
danr@cs.uiuc.edu

The makefile included with this distribution most probably requires GNU make.
In general, just type 'gmake' to compile the system, and 'gmake clean' to
remove all object files and binaries.  If you want to include SNoW's server
functionality in your build, use 'gmake SERVER=1'.  But do take a look at the
Makefile - you may find useful options or platform specific compilation
instructions.  (Just commenting or uncommenting a line or two.)  

The SNoW User's Guide is no longer included in the software distribution.  You
can download it separately from the webpage.  As of 1/6/04, the User's Guide
is completely current with respect to version  3.1.0.  The revision history
can also be a useful source of information about SNoW's new features.


